{:proof/problem-id "apm-t94A04", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\n## 1. TARGET SANITY CHECK\n\n- **mentions-problem-objects?** YES — X, U, V open sets, simply connected hypotheses, path-connected intersection, union = X.\n- **avoids-assuming-conclusion?** YES — `SimplyConnectedSpace X` is the conclusion, derived from the hypotheses.\n- **meaningful-without-prose?** YES — standalone topological theorem: union of simply connected opens with path-connected intersection is simply connected.\n- **notes:** NOT in Mathlib. `SimplyConnectedSpace` exists as a typeclass but no union theorem. The proof requires: (1) Lebesgue number lemma to subdivide loops (available in Mathlib as `IsCompact.exists_forall_open_ball_subset`), (2) path concatenation/homotopy machinery (partially available via `Path.Homotopy`), (3) the \"insert connecting paths\" trick (custom). This is a 50+ line Lean proof at minimum. The categorical van Kampen in Mathlib is unrelated (it's about colimit diagrams in category theory, not fundamental groups).\n\n## 2. PROOF-PLAN.EDN\n\n```clojure\n{:goal \"X = U ∪ V, U,V open sc, U∩V nonempty pc ⟹ X sc (without van Kampen).\"\n :terms\n [{:name \"simply connected\" :meaning \"π₁ = 0\" :needed-because \"hypothesis and conclusion\"}\n  {:name \"Lebesgue number\" :meaning \"δ-subdivision of loops\" :needed-because \"breaks loop into U/V pieces\"}\n  {:name \"connecting paths\" :meaning \"γₖ in U∩V from basepoint to subdivision points\" :needed-because \"converts pieces into loops in U or V\"}]\n :strategy\n [{:id :subdivide :formal-dependency \"Lebesgue number\" :informal-dependency \"split loop\" :why-this-now \"first step\" :lean-target \"subdivision\" :mathlib-status \"available\" :critical-path true}\n  {:id :insert-connectors :formal-dependency \"path-connectedness of U∩V\" :informal-dependency \"insert γₖ·γₖ⁻¹\" :why-this-now \"creates loops\" :lean-target \"loops in U/V\" :mathlib-status \"custom\" :critical-path true}\n  {:id :null-homotopy :formal-dependency \"sc of U,V\" :informal-dependency \"each loop contracts\" :why-this-now \"final step\" :lean-target \"α ≃ₕ const\" :mathlib-status \"Path.Homotopy available\" :critical-path true}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :pending :stage2 :pending :stage3 :pending :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n## 3. FORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n\n```clojure\n{:main-claim\n {:informal-claim \"X = U ∪ V, U,V open sc, U∩V nonempty pc ⟹ X sc.\"\n  :formal-name \"simplyConnected_of_union\"\n  :formal-target \"theorem simplyConnected_of_union {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {U V : Set X} (hU_open : IsOpen U) (hV_open : IsOpen V) (hUV : U ∪ V = Set.univ) (hU_sc : SimplyConnectedSpace U) (hV_sc : SimplyConnectedSpace V) (hUV_ne : (U ∩ V).Nonempty) (hUV_pc : IsPathConnected (U ∩ V)) : SimplyConnectedSpace X\"\n  :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true :meaningful-without-prose? true :notes \"NOT in Mathlib. Needs custom path subdivision proof.\"}}\n :alignments\n [{:formal-name \"simplyConnected_of_union\" :formal-statement \"... : SimplyConnectedSpace X\" :informal-clause \"Main claim\" :role :main-theorem}\n  {:formal-name \"loop_subdivision\" :formal-statement \"subdivision lemma\" :informal-clause \"Lebesgue number gives pieces in U or V\" :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**1. Why it's hard:** Students must construct the \"connecting paths\" carefully — each γₖ must stay in the RIGHT set (U, V, or U∩V) depending on where the subdivision point lies. The path-connectedness of U ∩ V is used only at U-to-V transitions, and forgetting this is the most common error. The Lebesgue number step is standard but students who don't know the lemma will struggle.\n\n**2. The key insight:** Subdivide the loop (Lebesgue number), then insert γₖ · γₖ⁻¹ identity pairs between pieces. This converts path SEGMENTS into LOOPS, each living in U or V. Simple connectivity kills each loop.\n\n**3. Complete proof:** 5 steps in execute.md — path-connectedness, Lebesgue subdivision, connecting paths, loop factoring, null-homotopy of factors.\n\n**4. Lean formalization:** Statement type-checks (1 sorry). `SimplyConnectedSpace X` concluded from `IsOpen U/V`, `SimplyConnectedSpace U/V`, `IsPathConnected (U ∩ V)`. The proof construction (~80 lines) needs the Lebesgue-number subdivision + path algebra + homotopy composition pipeline, which Mathlib has in pieces (Path, Path.Homotopy, IsPathConnected, Lebesgue number) but not composed.\n\n**5. What connects:**\n- **Seifert-van Kampen (simply connected case):** this IS van Kampen when π₁(U) = π₁(V) = 0. The full van Kampen gives π₁(X) as a pushout.\n- **Computing π₁(Sⁿ) = 0 for n ≥ 2:** cover Sⁿ by two hemispheres (both contractible, intersection Sⁿ⁻¹ path-connected for n ≥ 2). Immediate from this theorem.\n- **π₁(ℝⁿ \\ {0}) for n ≥ 3:** cover by two open half-spaces (both contractible, intersection path-connected). Simply connected.\n- **Exam-day field kit:** (1) Lebesgue number ⟹ finite subdivision of any loop. (2) Path-connectedness of U ∩ V is the crucial hypothesis — it provides the \"bridge\" paths. (3) Insert γₖ · γₖ⁻¹ to convert segments into loops. (4) Simply connected = every loop contracts.", :proof/extraction {:phases {:execute "```clojure\n{:goal \"X = U ∪ V, U,V open sc, U∩V nonempty pc ⟹ X sc (without van Kampen).\"\n :terms\n [{:name \"simply connected\" :meaning \"π₁ = 0\" :needed-because \"hypothesis and conclusion\"}\n  {:name \"Lebesgue number\" :meaning \"δ-subdivision of loops\" :needed-because \"breaks loop into U/V pieces\"}\n  {:name \"connecting paths\" :meaning \"γₖ in U∩V from basepoint to subdivision points\" :needed-because \"converts pieces into loops in U or V\"}]\n :strategy\n [{:id :subdivide :formal-dependency \"Lebesgue number\" :informal-dependency \"split loop\" :why-this-now \"first step\" :lean-target \"subdivision\" :mathlib-status \"available\" :critical-path true}\n  {:id :insert-connectors :formal-dependency \"path-connectedness of U∩V\" :informal-dependency \"insert γₖ·γₖ⁻¹\" :why-this-now \"creates loops\" :lean-target \"loops in U/V\" :mathlib-status \"custom\" :critical-path true}\n  {:id :null-homotopy :formal-dependency \"sc of U,V\" :informal-dependency \"each loop contracts\" :why-this-now \"final step\" :lean-target \"α ≃ₕ const\" :mathlib-status \"Path.Homotopy available\" :critical-path true}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :pending :stage2 :pending :stage3 :pending :stage4 :pending}}\n```", :integrate "(1) Lebesgue number ⟹ finite subdivision of any loop. (2) Path-connectedness of U ∩ V is the crucial hypothesis — it provides the \"bridge\" paths. (3) Insert γₖ · γₖ⁻¹ to convert segments into loops. (4) Simply connected = every loop contracts."}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :partial, :phase-count 2, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T94A04/Apm_v2_t94A04_1775045150581", :frame/id "apm-v2-t94A04-1775045150581", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T12:05:50.608105Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.T94A04.Apm_v2_t94A04_1775045150581", :proof/problem-id "t94A04", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94A04/apm-v2-t94A04-1775045150581", :artifacts {:proof-plan "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94A04/apm-v2-t94A04-1775045150581/proof-plan.edn", :formal-alignment "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94A04/apm-v2-t94A04-1775045150581/formal-alignment.edn", :changelog "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94A04/apm-v2-t94A04-1775045150581/changelog.edn", :execute-notes "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94A04/apm-v2-t94A04-1775045150581/execute.md", :workspace-readme "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94A04/apm-v2-t94A04-1775045150581/README.md", :workspac